\subsection{Mordell-Weil rank}
\begin{definition}\label{g2c.mordell_weil_rank}
\uses{ag.abelian_variety}
The Mordell-Weil theorem states that the set of rational points on an {{KNOWL('ag.abelian_variety', 'abelian variety')}} over a number field forms a finitely generated abelian group, hence isomorphic to a group of the form $T \oplus \Z^r$, where $T$ is a finite torsion group.  The integer $r\ge 0$ is the **Mordell-Weil rank** of the abelian variety.
\end{definition}


